body_html: Actually it should be a trivial patch to support this (need to change addInputs in torch/csrc/jit/tracer.cpp). We do have strings as first class values in the JIT right now, and they can be embedded as constants in the graphs.

body: Actually it should be a trivial patch to support this (need to change `addInputs` in `torch/csrc/jit/tracer.cpp`). We do have strings as first class values in the JIT right now, and they can be embedded as constants in the graphs.
